query: SELECT t1.category_id, t1.description, COUNT(*) as count_email FROM project.dataset.categories t1 LEFT JOIN project.dataset.customer_contacts t2 ON t1.category_id = t2.customer_id GROUP BY t1.category_id, t1.description ORDER BY count_email ASC;
description: This SQL query selects category_id, description from the categories table and computes the aggregate of all rows from the customer_contacts table as None. It performs a left join join between the categories and customer_contacts tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by count_email in asc order.

query: SELECT t1.preferred_contact_method, t1.email, t1.contact_id, COUNT(t2.stock_level) as count_stock_level FROM project.dataset.customer_contacts t1 INNER JOIN project.dataset.inventory t2 ON t1.customer_id = t2.product_id GROUP BY t1.preferred_contact_method, t1.email, t1.contact_id ORDER BY t1.contact_id ASC;

query: SELECT t1.last_name, t1.department_id, t1.hire_date, COUNT(t2.zip_code) as count_zip_code FROM project.dataset.employees t1 RIGHT JOIN project.dataset.locations t2 ON t1.employee_id = t2.location_id GROUP BY t1.last_name, t1.department_id, t1.hire_date ORDER BY t1.last_name DESC;

query: SELECT t1.status, t1.amount, COUNT(t2.return_date) as count_return_date FROM project.dataset.orders t1 INNER JOIN project.dataset.return_orders t2 ON t1.order_id = t2.order_id GROUP BY t1.status, t1.amount ORDER BY count_return_date DESC;
description: This SQL query selects status, amount from the orders table and computes the count of return_date from the return_orders table as count_return_date. It performs a inner join join between the orders and return_orders tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by count_return_date in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.state, t1.zip_code, AVG(t2.carrier) as avg_carrier FROM project.dataset.locations t1 RIGHT JOIN project.dataset.shipments t2 ON t1.location_id = t2.order_id GROUP BY t1.state, t1.zip_code ORDER BY t1.zip_code DESC;
description: This SQL query selects state, zip_code from the locations table and computes the avg of carrier from the shipments table as avg_carrier. It performs a right join join between the locations and shipments tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by zip_code in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.category_name, t1.description, MAX(t2.unit_price) as max_unit_price FROM project.dataset.categories t1 INNER JOIN project.dataset.products t2 ON t1.category_id = t2.category_id GROUP BY t1.category_name, t1.description ORDER BY t1.description DESC;
description: This SQL query selects category_name, description from the categories table and computes the max of unit_price from the products table as max_unit_price. It performs a inner join join between the categories and products tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by description in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.category_id, t1.stock, AVG(t2.return_date) as avg_return_date FROM project.dataset.products t1 LEFT JOIN project.dataset.return_orders t2 ON t1.product_id = t2.order_id GROUP BY t1.category_id, t1.stock ORDER BY avg_return_date DESC;
description: This SQL query selects category_id, stock from the products table and computes the avg of return_date from the return_orders table as avg_return_date. It performs a left join join between the products and return_orders tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by avg_return_date in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.order_id, t1.payment_date, t1.amount, MAX(t2.status) as max_status FROM project.dataset.payments t1 RIGHT JOIN project.dataset.return_orders t2 ON t1.order_id = t2.order_id GROUP BY t1.order_id, t1.payment_date, t1.amount ORDER BY max_status DESC;
description: This SQL query selects order_id, payment_date, amount from the payments table and computes the max of status from the return_orders table as max_status. It performs a right join join between the payments and return_orders tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by max_status in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.status, t1.customer_id, MIN(t2.stock_level) as min_stock_level FROM project.dataset.orders t1 LEFT JOIN project.dataset.inventory t2 ON t1.customer_id = t2.warehouse_id GROUP BY t1.status, t1.customer_id ORDER BY min_stock_level DESC;
description: This SQL query selects status, customer_id from the orders table and computes the min of stock_level from the inventory table as min_stock_level. It performs a left join join between the orders and inventory tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by min_stock_level in desc order.

query: SELECT t1.quantity, t1.product_id, AVG(t2.refund_amount) as avg_refund_amount FROM project.dataset.order_details t1 RIGHT JOIN project.dataset.return_orders t2 ON t1.order_id = t2.order_id GROUP BY t1.quantity, t1.product_id ORDER BY avg_refund_amount ASC;
description: This SQL query selects quantity, product_id from the order_details table and computes the avg of refund_amount from the return_orders table as avg_refund_amount. It performs a right join join between the order_details and return_orders tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by avg_refund_amount in asc order.

query: SELECT t1.sale_id, t1.product_id, t1.quantity, AVG(t2.preferred_contact_method) as avg_preferred_contact_method FROM project.dataset.sales t1 INNER JOIN project.dataset.customer_contacts t2 ON t1.product_id = t2.contact_id GROUP BY t1.sale_id, t1.product_id, t1.quantity ORDER BY avg_preferred_contact_method DESC;
description: This SQL query selects sale_id, product_id, quantity from the sales table and computes the avg of preferred_contact_method from the customer_contacts table as avg_preferred_contact_method. It performs a inner join join between the sales and customer_contacts tables on the relevant fields, groups the results by the selected columns, and orders the results by avg_preferred_contact_method in desc order.
